Estrazioni Lotto, Superenalotto e 10eLotto sabato 2 novembre ottobre 2019: i numeri vincenti, Jackpot oltre 29 milioni di euro
02 Nov 2019, 20:12 by Redazione



Estrazioni Lotto, Superenalotto e 10eLotto 2 novembre 2019. Eccoci puntuali con il nuovo appuntamento, il secondo della settimana, quello del martedì. Anche oggi tutto è pronto per le estrazioni di Lotto, Superenalotto e 10elotto in modo che qualche fortunato possa diventare milionario: il Superenalotto ha raggiunto infatti un jackpot pari a 29.224.884,84 euro. I numeri vincenti del Lotto, del Superenalotto e del 10elotto saranno pubblicati in questa pagina a partire dalle 20.00: si consiglia di ricaricare in continuazione la pagina per seguire la diretta.

text:
Dubnevich announced his intention to appeal the measure

02 Nov 2019, 20:30


MP Yaroslav Dubnevich, suspected of misappropriation of state funds in the amount of more than 93 million UAH, said he was going to file an appeal against the court decision.

He said this when asked by journalists whether he would appeal the court's decision.
Earlier, MP Yaroslav Dubnevych commented on the court's decision on a preventive measure in the form of a pledge of 100 million hryvnias.



Dubnevich will have 5 days to deposit bail. In case of non-introduction of the SAP and NABU, they can apply for a change of the preventive measure.
The prosecution demanded that Dubnevich be sentenced to 60 days in custody with an alternative to bail in excess of 93 million hryvnias. Prosecutors argued that being deprived of liberty can hide from the investigation or influence witnesses.
Dubnevich's lawyers, for their part, asked the court to allow the people's deputy to be bailed.
We will remind, on Friday, November 1, in Kiev the court in case of the People's Deputy Dubnevich began. Prosecutors insisted on the use of a pre-trial detention measure in the form of detention with an alternative to bail. A break was announced later until 11:30 Saturday, November 2.
It is known that on October 31 the Verkhovna Rada approved the submission of the Prosecutor General Ruslan Ryaboshapka for the People's Deputy Dubnevich. After that, the Attorney General handed Dubnevich a suspicion in the parliament hall. The deputy is suspected of crimes under Part 5 of Art. 191 of the Criminal Code of Ukraine (misappropriation, misappropriation of property or seizure of property by abuse of office).
